      "text": "vigilance side: - (i) To undertake study of existing procedures and practices prevailing in his Organisation with a view to identify those procedures or practices which provide a scope for corruption and require modification. (ii) To find out the causes of delay, the points at which delay occurs and devise suitable steps to minimize delays at different stages; (iii) To review the regulatory functions to see whether all of them are strictly necessary and whether the method of discharge of those functions is capable of improvement;",
      "page": 62,
      "docName": "Vigilance Manual (Updated 2021).pdf"
