      "text": "vigilance cases to CVC. ( CVC Circular No. 3(V)/99/14 dated 16.05.2001) 3.2.4 All serious cases of malpractices reported by CAG which are perceived to have a vigilance angle would also be sent to the Commission for examination and follow up action. On receiving such references from CAG, the Commission would take follow up action with the disciplinary authorities. In this way, it will be ensured that the cases of corruption and issues having a vigilance angle are not lost sight of and there is effective synergy between CAG and the Commission to strengthen the system to fight corruption. (CVC Circular No. 3(V)/99/14 dated 16.05.2001)",
