      "text": "to justify the imposition of the formal punishment of censure, it calls for some formal action, such as, the communication of a written or oral warning, admonition, reprimand or caution. Administration of a warning in such circumstances does not amount to a formal punishment. It is an administrative device in the hands of the superior authority for conveying its criticism and disapproval of the work or conduct of the person warned and for making it known to him that he has done something blame-worthy, with a view to enabling him to make an effort to remedy the defect and generally with a view to toning up efficiency and maintaining discipline. Where a Departmental proceeding has been completed and it is considered that the officer concerned deserves to be penalized, he should be awarded any of the statutory penalties mentioned in rules 11 of the",
      "page": 159,
      "docName": "Vigilance Manual (Updated 2021).pdf"
