      "text": "in the past is not sufficient. The statement of imputations should be precise and factual. In particular, in cases of any misconduct / misbehaviour, it should mention the conduct / behaviour expected or the rule violated. It would be improper to call an Investigating Officer\u2019s Report a statement of imputations. While drafting the statement of imputations, it would not be proper to mention the defence and enter into a discussion of the merits of the case. Wording of the imputations should be clear enough to justify the imputations in spite of the likely version of the Government servant concerned. 7.14 LIST OF WITNESSES A number of witnesses are usually examined during the course of the preliminary inquiry and their statements are recorded. The list of such witnesses should be carefully checked and only those witnesses who will",
